Inferences: - The DV’s explain 97% of the variability. But the model fails the OLS assumptions test, as we can see from the QQ plot and Residuals va fitted plot. Therefore this model is biased. - For the given data, P values for the remaining variables are high so we cannot reject the null hypothesis
